Unnecessary but neat: make this a decorator.
```
def RegisterExtraOutput(key):
    def decorate(builder):
        valid_extra_outputs[key] = builder

@RegisterExtraOutput("badpix")
class BadPixBuilder(ExtraOutputBuilder):
    ...
```

Using a switch statement with conditional assignment inside a loop seems a bit sketchy: it makes assumptions about the order the roles appear in and the possible values that might exist.

I would recommend instead doing a series of if-else statements like:

```javascript
if (apiUserData.roles.includes(UserKinds.ADMIN)) {
  kind = UserKinds.ADMIN;
} else if (apiUserData.roles.includes(UserKinds.COACH)) {
  kind = UserKinds.ADMIN;
} else {
  ...
}
```

Might be a little slower but much clearer in meaning.

